\#1 ACP is $30/mo, so you went to a slower plan to save $5? Or is that a typo? Best way to cut the ISP bill if there's competitors in your area is to just have them match each other's price or switch back and forth. Without competition, the next best way may be to cancel and sign up again under another name if they offer "$ off for x-months" promotions, kind of like what you did for your cell phone.

&#x200B;

\#4 2% is good, but it's not unparalleled. There are multiple 2% cards, including Citi DoubleCash and Fidelity Rewards. There are a few BofA cards that pay up to 2.625% if you have $100K in deposits or investments to qualify for the highest rewards tier. There's also an Alliant Credit Union Visa with 2.5% cash back if you keep $1K in checking.
